### Airbnb Clone API — request collection
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension (click "Send Request"),
### or copy these into Postman.
### After logging in, copy the returned token into the @token variable below.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@token = PASTE_TOKEN_HERE

### 0. Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### 1. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "Test User",
  "email": "test@airbnb.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "host"
}

### 2. Login (copy "token" from the response into @token above)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane@airbnb.com",
  "password": "password321"
}

### 3. Get my profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Get all accommodations (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/accommodations

### 5. Get accommodations filtered by location (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/accommodations?location=New York

### 6. Create an accommodation (host/admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/accommodations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Sunny Loft in Johannesburg",
  "location": "Johannesburg",
  "type": "Entire loft",
  "description": "Bright loft close to the city centre.",
  "guests": 3,
  "bedrooms": 1,
  "bathrooms": 1,
  "amenities": ["wifi", "kitchen"],
  "images": ["https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1502672260266-1c1ef2d93688"],
  "price": 200,
  "weeklyDiscount": 10,
  "cleaningFee": 40,
  "serviceFee": 35,
  "occupancyTaxes": 20
}

### 7. Get one accommodation by id (replace the id)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/accommodations/PASTE_ACCOMMODATION_ID

### 8. Update an accommodation (owner/admin)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/accommodations/PASTE_ACCOMMODATION_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "price": 250
}

### 9. Create a reservation (any logged-in user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accommodationId": "PASTE_ACCOMMODATION_ID",
  "checkIn": "2026-08-01",
  "checkOut": "2026-08-08",
  "guests": 2
}

### 10. My reservations (as a guest)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/user
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 11. Reservations on my listings (as a host)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/host
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 12. Delete a reservation
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/PASTE_RESERVATION_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 13. Delete an accommodation (owner/admin)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/accommodations/PASTE_ACCOMMODATION_ID
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
